Update CHANGELOGs

commit.message: CI - Also install numpy for python tests
Python - Improve and Test EncodeInput extraction
Rust - InputSequence can be built from std::borrow::Cow too
Python - Extract single pre-tokenized inputs from np.array
Python - InputSequence with references when possible

Rust - InputSequence also works with references

Now that encoding always works with string slices, we don't need to own the input. This makes it possible to provide both owned content and references

Remove Tokenizer::normalize

This is actually a legacy function that doesn't really make sense now, and is getting really difficult to keep. So we remove it.
Fix a few things on NormalizedString
Add the ability to encode with char offsets

WordPiece uses byte offsets

This also let us remove some allocations
Update PreTokenizers with the new interface

NormalizedString handles byte offsets

We also keep track of the original alignments while modifying the NormalizedString. This makes the conversion much more easier.
